properties.Name: ProductIndicatorType
properties.Description:
A means of categorizing Product Indicators by functions performed, characteristics or similar common characteristics.

Ex:
- Base unit level of the trade item hierarchy
- Item is intended for ultimate consumption
- Information provider considers trade item to be at a hierarchy level where orders will be accepted from customers
- Information provider considers trade item as a dispatch / shipping unit
- Information provider will include this trade item on an invoice
- The article is not a fixed quantity, quantity is variable and may be based on weight, length or volume
- Can be used as a display unit
- Trade Item is packed as a non-rectilinear pattern
- Package can be used as returnable package
- Trade Item is a service
- Trade Item is only offered during certain parts of the year
- Trade Item has price printed on the pack
